---
/**
 * Range Rules Page
 *
 * Safety rules and guidelines for all ranges.
 */
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Range Rules" description="Safety rules and guidelines for Austin Rifle Club ranges">
  <section class="py-8 md:py-12">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <h1 class="page-title mb-8 text-center">
        Range Rules & Safety Guidelines
      </h1>

      <div class="bg-red-50 dark:bg-red-900/30 border-2 border-red-200 dark:border-red-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-8">
        <h2 class="card-title text-xl text-red-800 dark:text-red-300 mb-4">The Four Cardinal Rules of Firearm Safety</h2>
        <ol class="list-decimal list-inside space-y-3 text-red-900">
          <li class="font-semibold">Treat all firearms as if they are loaded.</li>
          <li class="font-semibold">Never point a firearm at anything you are not willing to destroy.</li>
          <li class="font-semibold">Keep your finger off the trigger until ready to shoot.</li>
          <li class="font-semibold">Be sure of your target and what is beyond it.</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
          <h2 class="card-title text-xl text-accent mb-4">General Range Rules</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">1.</span> Eye and ear protection is required at all times on any range.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">2.</span> All firearms must be unloaded and cased when not on a firing line.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">3.</span> All members and guests must sign in at the clubhouse upon arrival.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">4.</span> Cease fire immediately when the command "CEASE FIRE" is given.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">5.</span> No handling of firearms during a cold range or cease fire.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">6.</span> Shoot only at authorized targets on your designated range.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">7.</span> No shooting at wildlife, birds, or any object other than targets.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">8.</span> No alcohol or drug use before or during shooting activities.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">9.</span> Clean up your area - police brass, remove targets, dispose of trash.</li>
            <li class="flex gap-2"><span class="text-green-600 font-bold">10.</span> Report any unsafe behavior or range damage to a board member.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
          <h2 class="card-title text-xl text-accent mb-4">Pistol Range Rules (Ranges A & B)</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>• Maximum caliber: .45 ACP / 10mm for centerfire, any rimfire</li>
            <li>• No rifle-caliber handguns (e.g., .223/5.56, .308)</li>
            <li>• Shoot only at targets placed at proper height on target stands</li>
            <li>• No shooting at the ground or into the air</li>
            <li>• Rapid fire is permitted with control (all rounds on target)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
          <h2 class="card-title text-xl text-accent mb-4">Rifle Range Rules (Range C)</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>• Use only the 100yd and 200yd berms as backstops</li>
            <li>• No tracer, incendiary, or armor-piercing ammunition</li>
            <li>• .50 BMG requires prior board approval</li>
            <li>• Ensure all rounds impact the berm - no shooting over</li>
            <li>• Benchrest shooting from covered positions only</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
          <h2 class="card-title text-xl text-accent mb-4">Action Bay Rules (Ranges H-L)</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>• 180-degree rule applies at all times</li>
            <li>• No shooting outside the bay berms</li>
            <li>• Holster draw permitted only with proper training certification</li>
            <li>• Steel targets: minimum 7 yards for pistol, 100 yards for rifle</li>
            <li>• Reset steel targets when finished</li>
            <li>• During matches, follow all Match Director instructions</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white dark:bg-stone-800 rounded-lg shadow-md p-6">
          <h2 class="card-title text-xl text-accent mb-4">Guest Policy</h2>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-700">
            <li>• Members may bring up to 4 guests per visit</li>
            <li>• All guests must sign the waiver at the clubhouse</li>
            <li>• Members are responsible for their guests at all times</li>
            <li>• Guests must remain with their sponsoring member</li>
            <li>• Same guest may visit up to 3 times per year before membership is required</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/30 border border-amber-200 dark:border-amber-700 rounded-lg p-6">
          <h2 class="card-title text-xl text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 mb-4">Violations</h2>
          <p class="text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-200">
            Safety violations are taken seriously. Depending on severity, violations may result in:
          </p>
          <ul class="mt-3 space-y-1 text-amber-900 dark:text-amber-200">
            <li>• Verbal warning and education</li>
            <li>• Written warning on file</li>
            <li>• Temporary suspension of membership</li>
            <li>• Permanent revocation of membership</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="mt-4 text-amber-800 dark:text-amber-300 text-sm">
            All members have the right and responsibility to call a cease fire and address safety concerns.
            Report serious violations to the Board of Directors.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 text-center">
        <p class="text-muted text-sm">
          Last updated: January 2024 | Questions? Contact{' '}
          <a href="mailto:info@austinrifleclub.org" class="link-accent">
            info@austinrifleclub.org
          </a>
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
